post_text: COACH SPOTLIGHT: "My absolute most favorite moment was during my first year of coaching. The Varsity Pom Team took 1st place out of ten teams at USA Spirit Regionals. After a tumultuous start to the season, it was a beautiful and completely unexpected reminder of the importance of teamwork and dedication for the girls and for the coaching staff. I still cry every time I see the video of the team's reaction at that awards ceremony! That win transformed the mentality of the team, which ultimately earned that same routine a spot at Finals at USA Spirit Nationals for the first time in school history." - Bailey Moore, POM Head Coach at Queen Creek High School!

post_text: We are proud to be a part of such a wonderful community! #QCLeads
shared_text:
Queen Creek Town Hall
September 1 at 7:40 PM ¬∑

Happy Founders‚Äô Month!
This year, we are celebrating our heritage throughout the month of September with drive-in watch parties, scavenger hunts, Battle of the Badge, and more - including #TidbitTuesday! Check back each Tuesday for a new tidbit about QC!

Queen Creek was incorporated on Sept. 5, 1989 after years of hard work by the "Queen Creek Five" and others along the way. The "Queen Creek Five" are known as the Founding Fathers and include Robert Eberle, Paul Gardner, Ralph Pomeroy, Mark Schnepf and Steve Sossaman. You can learn more about their efforts by visiting the plaque at Picket Post Square (NW corner of Ellsworth Rd & Ocotillo Rd).

Faith Mather Sossaman Elementary
August 16 at 9:13 PM ¬∑

Tomorrow we will be welcoming our Sabercats for their first day of in-person learning. Please remember:
1. Students must wear a face mask on campus.
2. Students will enter through the front gate and go directly to their classrooms.
3. Parents will not be able to walk their child to their classrooms. We will have staff helping them get to the correct location.
4. Parents are responsible for screening their children at home and not sending them to school if they are sick.

We are doing everything we can to make this a safe return for all our students and staff and ask for your support.

ALL QCUSD STUDENTS WILL BEGIN ON-LINE LEARNING, no matter the option you chose, ON AUGUST 3.

‚úÖIf you chose the short-term online learning option that transitions into in-person instruction, you and your student will want to take part in virtual Meet the Teacher happening this week. Wednesday is virtual Meet the Teacher for JR High & High School and Thursday is virtual Meet the Teacher for Elementary. See your individual school site for specific details.

‚úÖPlease note that families who chose long-term online learning through the Queen Creek Virtual Academy (this option is a semester or the entire school year) will not see a schedule or teacher in StudentVue/ParentVue and information about starting will be coming soon!

As a reminder, no matter which option you chose, all students will begin the upcoming school year online, August 3rd.

post_text: STUDENT SUCCESS!
shared_text:
Queen Creek High School
July 13 at 6:14 PM ¬∑

STUDENT SUCCESS: This past June the International Thespian Society held their annual National Competition. Of course due to the pandemic it had to be done online but that didn't stop 5 Queen Creek Theater students from participating.

Hugh Hucknull and Scotty Hagen earned a Superior for their Duo Acting scene.

Sabrina Harding earned an Excellent for her Monologues

Lennon VanAusdal earned an Excellent for her Make-up Design

Also at this event Juniors were able to audition for colleges across the country. After the auditions, schools are able to "callback" the students to interview and offer acceptance into their theater programs.

Sabrina Harding received 25 college callbacks

Hugh Hucknull received 22 college callbacks

And Jasmyn Gade received 18 college callbacks

post_text: EXCEPTIONAL PERSONNEL: This year QCUSD introduced the Awards of Excellence. Each school site named a Teacher and Support Staff Member of the Year from their school. From the 22 school site award recipients, a Teacher of the Year and Support Staff Member of the Year was named for the entire district. Our hope was to honor these award recipients at a nice dinner emceed by ABC15 Arizona news anchor Danielle Lerner, but due to COVID19 those plans changed. However, the district created this special video tribute to recognize the amazing work of the Awards of Excellence recipients. One more time, please help us congratulate, Tami Vega and Kris Wells! #QCLeads

post_text:
EXCEPTIONAL PERSONNEL: At QCUSD we value, support, and recognize excellence in all of our employees. This year we created an opportunity to recognize this excellence throughout the district by allowing staff members to anonymously nominate their colleagues for the Awards of Excellence. This is the first year of the award in the district.

Criteria was created using a four-prong approach: achieves excellence, leads with integrity, empowers others around them, displays PBIS Values (Be Kind, Be Respectful, Show Integrity). A Teacher of the Year and Support Staff Member of the Year was named for each site.

From those 22 award recipients, the Teacher of the Year and the Support Staff Member of the Year for the entire district was named at the April 28 Board Meeting.

Congratulations to Faith Mather Sossaman Elementary 3rd-grade teacher Tami Vega for being named the QCUSD Teacher of the Year and Queen Creek Middle School Administrative Assistant Kris Wells for being named the QCUSD Support Staff Member of the Year! #QCLeads
text:
EXCEPTIONAL PERSONNEL: At QCUSD we value, support, and recognize excellence in all of our employees. This year we created an opportunity to recognize this excellence throughout the district by allowing staff members to anonymously nominate their colleagues for the Awards of Excellence. This is the first year of the award in the district.

Criteria was created using a four-prong approach: achieves excellence, leads with integrity, empowers others around them, displays PBIS Values (Be Kind, Be Respectful, Show Integrity). A Teacher of the Year and Support Staff Member of the Year was named for each site.

From those 22 award recipients, the Teacher of the Year and the Support Staff Member of the Year for the entire district was named at the April 28 Board Meeting.

Congratulations to Faith Mather Sossaman Elementary 3rd-grade teacher Tami Vega for being named the QCUSD Teacher of the Year and Queen Creek Middle School Administrative Assistant Kris Wells for being named the QCUSD Support Staff Member of the Year! #QCLeads

Eastmark High School is proud to recognize our two QCUSD Awards of Excellence winners:
Certified (Teaching) Staff: Allison Smith

At QCUSD we value, support and recognize excellence in all of our employees. Achieves excellence

post_text:
EXCEPTIONAL PERSONNEL: We are thrilled to announce Newell Barney Middle School Assistant Principal/Athletic Director Carl Holgerson has been named the Middle School Athletic Director of the Year by the Arizona Interscholastic Athletic Administrators Association. Carl is the first recipient of this award, as the AIAAA recently voted to expand AD of the Year recognitions to the Middle School level.

Carl has spent well over a decade supporting student-athletes, and if you know Carl, you have heard the phrase "I'll do that right now."

We are blessed to have Carl on our team, but more so we are thankful to have him in our lives. The late Newell Barney would be so proud of Carl's recognition, and the entire QCUSD community would like to echo that pride with a huge congratulations!! #QCLeads #QueenCreek AZPreps365
